Usage: gui_zoom_ctd [-help] [-id <string>] [-vertical_range {<ymin ymax>}] [ -in  | -out  | -selected  ]

-help                             # Prints out the command usage
-id <string>                      # Specify the window ID of the CTD window
                                  # which need to zoom. (string, optional)
-in                               # Zoom in. (bool, optional)
-out                              # Zoom out. (bool, optional)
-selected                         # Zoom to enclose all selected objects.
                                  # (bool, optional)
-vertical_range {<ymin ymax>}     # Zoom to a specific vertical range. If CTD
                                  # is in timing-based mode,  the window will
                                  # zoom to the clock tree parts where latency
                                  # is between ymin and ymax, the unit is the
                                  # same as global timing unit;  if CTD is in
                                  # unit delay mode, the window will zoom to
                                  # the clock tree parts where stage depth is
                                  # between ymin and ymax. The window only
                                  # zooms in vertical. (string, optional)